xible resealable pouch products accounted for  million in revenue in fiscal  and  million in the first quarter of  and were part of sunopta’s healthy snacks platform in its consumer products segment sunopta opened foodpouch manufacturing operations in upper macungie in  and added a  million expansion in late  to add aseptic processing for soy almond and similar milk products aseptic processing production will continue at the plant the company did not respond to a question on how the equipment sale would affect employment at the facility although dave colo ceo of sunopta issued a statement “i want to thank all of our employees involved in the flexible resealable pouch operations for their hard work and dedication” colo said “each employee has contributed to our goal of bringing wellbeing to life in their own way and has had a meaningful impact at sunopta” as of february  the company reported adding  jobs for aseptic processing on top of the  employees it had previously on the resealable pouch production line the equipment sale is expected to be completed in the fourth quarter this year you may have missed • the top andahalf deal killers when trying to sell a business • pr stunts can work – if you have a plan and stay on brand • cyber money better spent on attack deterrence not recovery • turnaround pro touts honesty communication share this story on twitter facebook google linkedin   stacy wescoe writer and online editor stacy wescoe has her finger on the pulse of the business community in the greater lehigh valley and keeps you uptodate with technology and trends plus what coworkers and competitors are talking about around the water cooler — and on social media she can be reached at stacywlvbcom or  ext  follow her on twitter at morestacy and on facebook circle stacy wescoe on google leave a comment your name validation comment please note all comments will be reviewed and may take up to  hours to appear on the site post comment view comment policy comments also on 